fix: cascade unified color system to all app sections

This commit eliminates every hardcoded hex color across the remaining
pages and replaces all .toLocaleString() financial displays with the
unified fmtAdaptive() utility. All sections now share the same visual
language as the dashboard.

Pages updated:
- Transactions: hero banner gradient now uses var(--success/primary/teal)
  and var(--danger/purple/teal) tokens. Net balance adapts between
  positive/negative states with CSS vars. All KES amounts use fmtAdaptive.
- Budgets: budgetStyle() helper completely rewritten to use var(--danger),
  var(--warning), var(--success) for colors, border accents, bar gradients
  and glow shadows. Hero banner gradient uses var(--warning/purple/primary).
  All amounts use fmtAdaptive with adaptive font-size at 1M and 10M.
- Net Worth: hero banner gradient uses var(--success/primary/purple) or
  var(--danger/purple/teal) depending on net worth sign. All asset and
  liability amounts use fmtAdaptive. Token vars throughout.
- Loans: loanStyle() helper rewritten with var(--danger/warning/success)
  for colors and bar gradients. Hero banner gradient uses var(--danger/purple/
  teal) or var(--teal/primary/purple). All loan balances, original amounts,
  and monthly payment figures use fmtAdaptive with adaptive font-size.

The result: the entire app now has one unified visual identity. Switch
theme, scale a number to 10M, view any page - it is always coherent.
